republican george bush heading to his first 
facetoface encounter with democratic presidential opponent 
michael dukakis has cleared much of this weeks schedule to bone 
up for next sundays debate 
bush is keeping a light campaign itinerary taking day trips out 
of washington and returning in the afternoons to closet himself 
with his debate coaches 
bush today was speaking to the bucks county chamber of commerce 
in pennsylvania after a meeting in philadelphia with roman catholic 
archbishop anthony bevilaqua and retired cardinal john krol 
on tuesday he travels to new jersey to visit the annin flag 
company a business he has cited in speeches as a sign that 
patriotism has been on the rise during the reagan presidency bush 
says flag sales were down when jimmy carter was president but that 
after reagans election business was booming again 
later in the week bush plans a brief campaign trip to texas 
