<TEXT>
here at a glance is a look at burma where military commander 
saw maung overthrew civilian president maung maung 
the land burma on the bay of bengal is nearly the size of 
texas and shares frontiers with bangladesh india china thailand 
and laos resources include fertile soil teak and other hardwoods 
oil and several important minerals rangoon with a population of 
35 million is the capital and largest city mandalay the 
secondlargest city and last capital of the burmese kings is of 
historical and cultural interest burma has a tropical monsoon 
climate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people about twothirds of the 38 million people are 
ethnic burmans who are related to tibetans important minorities 
include karens shans chins kachins chinese and indian about 85 
percent of the people practice buddhism with minorities adhering 
to islam and christianity 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy per capita income is about 180 a year making 
burma one of the worlds poorest nations an agricultural country 
burma once was the worlds leading rice exporter but it experienced 
food shortages in 1987 burmas debt has climbed to more than 3 
billion 
the black market fueled by smuggled goods from thailand and 
china overshadows the official economy 
burmas economic failure is generally attributed to poor 
government management and a crippling war against several ethnic 
minorities seeking autonomy japan and west germany are major aid 
donors and the united states has a modest assistance program 
mainly in the antidrug area 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history the burmese arrived from tibet before the 9th century 
displacing earlier cultures burmas golden age was the 12th 
century when its kings built the spectacular temples of pagan 
britain ruled it from 1886 to 1948 after a postindependence 
experiment with democracy a military coup in 1962 brought gen ne 
win to power he imposed isolationism and socialized the economy 
ne win resigned july 23 after antigovernment demonstrations he 
was replaced by retired army gen sein lwin who resigned aug 13 
after further antigovernment riots maung maung a 
westerneducated lawyer on aug 19 became burmas first civilian 
president since the 1962 coup saw maung defense minister since 
july ousted maung maung in a military coup sunday 
burma seeks to maintain a strictly neutralist policy and keep 
out most foreign influences including joint ventures with foreign 
companies it has been nicknamed asias hermit tourists are 
allowed to stay only one week 
</TEXT>
