<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap prosper avril a quiet studious 
50yearold career soldier has emerged from the shadows of haitian 
politics to proclaim himself president of this violencewracked 
republic 
avril a thin bespectacled man looked more like a college 
professor than a soldier when he announced on national television 
sunday that he was persuaded by the presidential guard to head 
the military government only his dress uniform and military cap 
gave him away 
i find myself forced to accept the office of president of the 
military government the softspoken new president said in the 
same breath avril a brigadier general and adjutant general 
announced he had promoted himself to lieutenant general 
avril a career soldier of humble origin was born in the small 
town of thomageau a short distance from the capital but close 
associates say he is extremely intelligent and has used the army to 
manipulate his way to power and riches he is believed to be a 
millionaire 
his career has always been linked closely to those who wield 
power in haiti 
early on he caught the eye of francois papa doc duvalier 
the country doctor who founded the duvalier political dynasty more 
than 30 years ago 
avril graduated at the head of his class from the military 
academy during the first year of duvaliers rule he was a 
classmate of brig gen williams regala who later would be part of 
the fiveman provisional government which ruled haiti immediately 
after duvaliers son jeanclaude duvalier fled to exile on feb 
7 1986 
always a survivor avril served under both duvaliers and as a 
political adviser to lt gen henri namphy who headed the junta 
that replaced jeanclaude 
avril is said to get along well with just about everyone and to 
have no enemies in the army which is considered a rare 
accomplishment he was retired by jeanclaude near the end of his 
regime due to a conflict between avril and interior minister roger 
lafontant a man known for his brutal methods of maintaining law 
and order 
although he joined the junta as an adviser avril was forced to 
resign in early 1986 by massive protest demonstrations seeking the 
ouster of all former associates of the duvaliers 
with the rank of colonel he became inspector of the 
presidential guard a job he kept when president leslie manigat 
took office on feb 7 1988 after being elected in 
militarycontrolled elections boycotted by the most popular 
candidates 
avril then helped namphy regain power in a bloodless coup in 
june 
namphy promoted him to brigadier general and appointed him 
adjutant general of the army an administrative post 
avril has always been a staunch supporter of the duvalier 
regime one of the most oppressive dictatorships in the world until 
it was toppled in 1986 he was believed to have had an office at 
the national bank where he managed the special bank accounts of 
jeanclaude 
avril is married to a nurse 
he has no reputation for cruelty and those who know him say he 
has two attributes that are rare in the army a keen political mind 
and the ability to listen to others 
the president guard sergeant who announced on television that 
namphy had been overthrown introduced avril as the most honest 
man in the army 
many in haiti took heart from his promise that dialogue will 
be honored for the sake of national reconciliation which was 
interpreted by many as an offer to negotiate with the democratic 
opposition 
this event has come at the right moment to put an end to a 
government which was going to lead the country to an abyss we 
greet with satisfaction the first declaration of the new 
president said an unexpected admirer max bourjolly 
secondincommand of the haitian communist party 
