<TEXT>
what ever happened to the revolutionaries of the late 60s and 
early 70s the question bubbles below the placid surface of 1988 
and one answer has arrived in a riveting new film 
running on empty offers a story so current it is mimicked in 
real life even as it is released the recent surrender in oakland 
calif of a 60s fugitive who gave up for the good of her children 
is eerily close to the story naomi foner has written for the screen 
the film is the story of annie and arthur pope christine lahti 
and judd hirsch fugitive leftovers from the days of violent 
antivietnam war protest more significantly it is the story of 
their brilliant musically gifted teenage son danny river 
phoenix 
running on empty is certain to be remembered as the film 
that made phoenix a star the teenager with the 60s name has 
intensity and dramatic control far beyond his years 
under sidney lumets masterful direction the viewer is drawn 
quickly into the odyssey of the popes who are wanted for the 1971 
bombing of a defense intallation in which a janitor was maimed 
since then theyve been on the lam moving from town to town as 
the fbi came close teaching their two young sons to live a lie 
the boys have new names in each new school and are careful never to 
appear in a class picture the parents hold jobs and derive 
substantial support from a vague underground network the ruse 
works for 17 years 
the crisis that propels this film is dannys impending high 
school graduation his musical gift which demands further schooling 
and his romance with the daughter of his music teacher young 
martha plimpton as the girlfriend plays in perfect counterpoint to 
phoenixs sensitive engaging danny 
the parents must decide whether to uproot danny one more time 
hirsch with the least sympathetic role as the selfinvolved 
aging radical father summons up the most realistic reflection of 
the radical life as it was 
lahti an actress who displays new depths with every 
performance has the movies most affecting scene in a reunion with 
the grieving father she left behind there wasnt a dry eye in the 
house at a recent screening 
tackling such a prickly subject has pitfalls and running on 
empty has its flaws the resolutions are too pat the kids 
resilience strains credulity and the norman rockwell style settings 
including a high school with the grandeur of harvard are a bit 
much the rosy glow of conservative america pervades this film 
the political passion beneath the popes predicament is barely 
explored lahti offers the lame explanation it was over when the 
war was over 
but running on empty aims to win our hearts rather than our 
minds and it does that with great success 
running on empty is rated pg13 for its general subject 
matter and the sexual affair between teenagers 
