turning to the pop music market she decided to change her first 
name supposedly ignorant of the sam phillips who founded sun 
records 
the 26yearold california native has a littlegirl voice and a 
knack for writing memorable melodies with producer and boyfriend 
tbone burnett shes crafted an inventive record rich with 1960s 
influences 
the wistful she cant tell time sounds like an outtake from 
the beatles rubber soul while remorse quotes liberally 
from the fab fours shes a woman 
like most albums the indescribable wow has its strong songs 
and filler but phillips and burnett save their most imaginative 
arrangements for the weak songs keeping boredom at bay 
what do i do for instance is so slight it would probably 
sound incomplete if strummed on an acoustic guitar burnett and 
guest van dyke parks turn it into a minioperetta with a full 
orchestra and dreamy staggered vocals 
holding on to the earth is sinistersounding with a farfisa 
organ and what sounds like a sitar 
burnett is savvy enough to let the strong material stand almost 
by itself phillips voice is so seductive in i dont want to 
fall in love that she wont be able to say the same for her 
listeners i dont know how to say goodbye to you and i cant 
stop crying are two other heartbreakers 
phillips and burnett make a fine studio team as any lover of 
classic pop music will be able to attest 
by david bauder associated press writer 
