john cheek was hired by the metropolitan opera 
in 1977 after james levine heard him praised often enough to 
audition him he was hired by the new york city opera nine years 
later after beverly sills heard his voice in her dentists office 
its more usual for an upandcoming american opera singer to 
move from the new york city opera to the met 
but cheek this season will sing at both places to the 
satisfaction of himself the two opera companies and the public 
how he came to be engaged by miss sills is an improbable story 
cheek says but its the one she told him so he believes it 
visiting her dentist she complained about the noise of the 
drill he handed her earphones and challenged her to guess who was 
singing two of the devils arias from faust she couldnt 
told it was john cheek whom shed heard but in roles not 
requiring personality projection she immediately called cheeks 
manager and said she was interested in him for mefistofele 
this season at the new york city opera the 6foot3 
bassbaritone will sing three evil title roles in mefistofele 
