its big customers on monday announced faster mainframe computers 
as well as software that speeds up transactions such as airline 
reservations and banking 
however unisys announced a threemonth delay in its previously 
announced 2200400 computers which will be available by march 
instead of by the end of 1988 
the new 2200600 mainframe computers which had been delayed two 
or three years are expected to slow or stop the defection of 
unisys customers to other makers of big computers particularly 
international business machines corp said jay stevens an analyst 
for dean witter reynolds inc 
the new machines are the successors to the 110090 computers of 
sperry corp which burroughs corp took over two years ago to form 
unisys 
the 1100 series is a favorite with banks and airlines both of 
which are heavy users of a style of computing called online 
transaction processing unisys said it could achieve an 
industrybest 6500 transactions per second by closely tying 
together four computers each containing four processors 
unisys said the 2200600 computers complete the renewal of the 
1100 line which it promised at the time of the burroughssperry 
merger 
the computers use semiconductors and packaging technology from 
hitachi ltd but unisys said it intends eventually to drop its 
reliance on the japanese company 
