csx corp said monday it would buy back up 
to 60 million of its common shares and sell off two natural gas 
units in a billiondollar restructuring that will allow the company 
to concentrate on its transportation business 
csx said it would begin repurchasing shares this week through a 
dutch auction in which shareholders are invited to offer their 
holdings at a price between 28 and 33 per share the company will 
choose one price and purchase up to 40 million shares offered at or 
below that price 
depending on market conditions the remainder of the 60 million 
shares would be purchased on the open market or in private 
negotiations officials said 
at 33 a share the restructuring would cost csx a total of 
198 billion 
investors reacted enthusiastically to the csx announcement and 
bid the companys stock up 375 a share to 3050 in new york 
stock exchange composite trading 
